    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-03T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9159: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-03T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 3, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>362. Our 358, August 3, noon.<note n="36" xml:id="d341fn36">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. We learn from reliable source that during Han Fu Chu’s<note n="37"
                        xml:id="d341fn37">Chairman of Shantung Provincial Government.</note> visit
                    to Nanking he gave National Government satisfactory assurances of his
                    determination to resist any Japanese military activity in Central China and to
                    cooperate fully with Central Government troops. According to this source, he
                    promised the Generalissimo that he would oppose by force any incursion of
                    Japanese troops into the province or the landing of Japanese naval parties at
                    Tsingtao.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Tokyo. Peiping, Tsingtao and Tsinanfu being informed.
                    Code text to Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
